name: Apple Siri lawsuit settlement
summary: Apple has agreed to pay $95 million to settle a class action lawsuit that accused Siri of recording conversations without consent. The lawsuit alleged that Siri had been eavesdropping on users' conversations and collecting data on their activities. Apple has denied any wrongdoing, but the settlement will allow users who believe their privacy was invaded to make a claim for up to $20 per device. To be eligible, users must have an Apple device with Siri enabled and have used Siri at least once between October 21, 2011, and February 18, 2019. Users who meet the criteria will be notified via email or mail and can submit a claim online or by mail.

name: Clarence Thomas
summary: In a recent decision, the US judicial body declined to refer Supreme Court Justice Clarence Thomas to the Justice Department for an ethics investigation. The move was met with criticism from some quarters, who argued that it undermines public trust in the judiciary. The decision was made despite allegations of ethical misconduct against Thomas, including his wife's involvement in efforts to overturn the 2020 election results. The judicial body also declined to refer Justice Ketanji Brown Jackson to the Justice Department, citing unsubstantiated allegations of ethical violations. One Democratic Senator expressed disapproval of the decision, arguing that it creates a double standard for ethical scrutiny of judges.

name: LaLiga
summary: La Liga news has been dominated by transfer market developments, with Barcelona's attempts to sign Dani Olmo and Pau Victor dominating headlines. The club has been thwarted in its efforts, however, as La Liga has rejected their registration attempt. This decision has led to reports that the clubs in the league may pursue legal action against La Liga if the decision is not overturned. Despite the transfer saga, the league has also released the updated standings and fixtures for the 2023/24 season, with Real Madrid sitting atop the table after their 2-1 win over Valencia. The league has also announced the launch of a new podcast in Vietnam and released statistics and predictions for the upcoming campaign.

name: Charlie Morton
summary: Charlie Morton, a veteran starting pitcher, has signed a one-year contract with the Baltimore Orioles. The 41-year-old right-hander, who was a key part of the Atlanta Braves' World Series victory last year, joins a young Orioles team hoping to compete for an AL Wild Card berth. The signing is praised by some as a shrewd move for the Orioles, who add an experienced and successful arm to their rotation, while others criticize it as a lackluster replacement for the highly effective Corbin Burnes.

name: Quadrantids meteor showers
summary: The Quadrantid meteor shower, set to peak in early 2025, will be one of the first significant celestial events of the year. Known as one of the strongest meteor showers, it is expected to produce up to 120 meteors per hour at its peak. Observers are encouraged to look to the northeastern sky during the hours after midnight for optimal viewing. The meteor shower is set to reach its peak in the early morning hours and will be best viewed from areas with minimal light pollution.
